TITLE: Why Ford says new high-tech features for its Super Duty trucks will save marriages
SUMMARY: The 2023 Ford Super Duty lineup is designed to ease difficulties with some of the vehicles' most important functions: towing and carrying/hauling.

TITLE: Student loan relief is gone for millions of Americans — here's what it means for retailers
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court striking down Biden's student debt cancelation plan, and the resumption of payments, will add more pressure to already cautious consumers.

TITLE: Goldman in talks to offload Apple credit card, savings products to American Express, source says
SUMMARY: Goldman Sachs is looking to unload its Apple financial products as part of a wider retreat from its failed consumer banking initiatives.

TITLE: Flight disruptions continue on peak July Fourth travel day, with United faring the worst
SUMMARY: The TSA expects to screen 17.7 million people from June 29 through July 5, peaking on Friday at more than 2.8 million people.

TITLE: JPMorgan, Wells Fargo and Morgan Stanley to boost dividends after clearing Fed stress test
SUMMARY: Big banks like JPMorgan are planning to increase their quarterly dividend payouts after clearing the annual Federal Reserve stress test earlier this week.

TITLE: Fox News to pay $12 million to settle fired producer Abby Grossberg's lawsuit
SUMMARY: Fox News agreed to pay $12 million to settle with ex-producer Abby Grossberg, who alleged network coerced her into giving misleading testimony on Dominion.

TITLE: Medicare will allow pharmaceutical companies to publicly discuss drug price negotiations
SUMMARY: Drugmakers had sued the federal government, arguing that the "gag order" violated the First Amendment.

TITLE: It's not just Tesla and Rivian — electric batteries are also shaking up the landscaping aisle
SUMMARY: Home Depot and Lowe's are trying to capitalize on more consumers switching to battery-powered tools for landscaping lawns, golf courses and parks.

TITLE: ESPN lays off about 20 on-air personalities including NBA analysts Jeff Van Gundy and Jalen Rose
SUMMARY: ESPN is laying off about 20 on-air employees as part of a broader cost cutting effort.

TITLE: Little-known NJ baby retailer tentatively wins rights to Buy Buy Baby's IP for $15.5 million
SUMMARY: Little-known baby retailer Dream on Me Industries has tentatively won the rights to Buy Buy Baby ahead of an auction for all of the chain's assets.

TITLE: Indiana Jones hits theaters for one last adventure, but box office prospects look shaky
SUMMARY: Box office analysts predict Disney's "Indiana Jones and the Dial of Destiny" will open to between $60 million and $65 million at the domestic box office.

TITLE: People should stop taking Ozempic, Wegovy obesity drugs before surgery, doctors group says
SUMMARY: Patients taking diabetes and weight loss drugs during anesthesia may be at increased risk of serious complications like nausea and vomiting, the ASA said.

TITLE: House hunting is already tough. Guess what? It's about to get harder
SUMMARY: In the last week of June, the number of homes for sale fell below year-ago levels for the first time in 59 weeks.

TITLE: Workers at Boeing 737 supplier approve labor deal, ending strike
SUMMARY: Spirit AeroSystems halted production at the Wichita, Kansas, plant last week.

TITLE: These retailers will take over Bed Bath & Beyond's 'top-notch' store leases
SUMMARY: Burlington Stores is set to take over 50 former Bed Bath & Beyond locations after the home goods retailer auctioned its leases.

TITLE: Former Pfizer employee charged with insider trading on unreleased Covid pill data
SUMMARY: The DOJ said the former employee and his close friend sold their Pfizer call options at "significant profits" totaling more than $350,000.

TITLE: Southwest pilots' union lays groundwork for potential strike with labor talks at an impasse
SUMMARY: Southwest's pilots' union is seeking to be released from federal mediation, a step toward a potential strike.

TITLE: Overstock.com shares spike 20% after company announces Bed Bath & Beyond website rebrand
SUMMARY: Overstock CEO Jonathan Johnson said the Bed Bath & Beyond name better aligns with the company's products and maintains good brand awareness.

TITLE: Hepatitis C cure is not reaching overwhelming majority of patients due to financial barriers
SUMMARY: Hepatitis C is often referred to as the silent killer because the initial infection has few to no symptoms.

TITLE: Polestar is the latest EV maker to announce a move to Tesla's North American charging standard
SUMMARY: Polestar owners will get access to Tesla's North American charging network starting in mid-2024.

TITLE: CDC recommends RSV vaccines from Pfizer, GSK for adults 60 and older
SUMMARY: The CDC said the shots from Pfizer and GSK are expected to be available this fall, when RSV – along with Covid and the flu – begins to spread at higher levels.

TITLE: Federal Reserve says 23 biggest banks weathered severe recession scenario in stress test
SUMMARY: Begun in the aftermath of the 2008 financial crisis, the Fed's annual stress test dictates how much capital the industry can return to shareholders.

TITLE: Overstock.com will change website name to Bed Bath & Beyond as deal closes
SUMMARY: Overstock.com has completed its acquisition of Bed Bath & Beyond's intellectual property and plans to move its website under Bed Bath's domain.

TITLE: As drugmakers race to develop the next big weight loss pill, Eli Lilly may have an edge
SUMMARY: For now, Eli Lilly's orforglipron appears to be the top contender in the weight loss pill space due to its strong efficacy data and ease of use.

TITLE: Doubt grows over Buy Buy Baby sale process as parent Bed Bath & Beyond splits auction
SUMMARY: Failed home goods retailer Bed Bath & Beyond will host two separate auctions for its Buy Buy Baby chain as interest in keeping the banner's stores open wanes.

TITLE: Zaslav brings in Spielberg, Scorsese, Anderson to help curate TCM film lineup after shake-up
SUMMARY: Warner Bros. Discovery will have Martin Scorsese, Steven Spielberg and Paul Thomas Anderson give their input on cable-TV film channel TCM.

TITLE: Fanatics increases its offer to $225 million to acquire PointsBet's U.S. assets
SUMMARY: Fanatics outbids DraftKings to acquire the U.S. assets of sports betting site PointsBet.

TITLE: Mortgage demand grows, driven by sales of new homes
SUMMARY: While applications for mortgages to buy a home rose week to week, they were still down more than 20% compared with a year earlier.

TITLE: The Inform Act just took effect — here's how it aims to target organized retail theft
SUMMARY: The Inform Act, a bipartisan bill targeting organized retail theft that takes effect Tuesday, requires online marketplaces to disclose the identity of sellers.

TITLE: Severe weather, FAA shortfalls kick off rocky start to summer air travel
SUMMARY: United's CEO blamed FAA staffing shortages for worsening flight disruptions over the weekend.
